result.execSummary:
The defendant Aleida Dominguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Aleida Dominguez is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Aleida Dominguez was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
ADDRESS INFO for Aleida Dominguez
Current: PO Box 5301, Brownsville, TX 78521 United States  (Effective: 03-29-2016)
Prior: 275 E John St, Markesan, WI 53946 

Given by defendant in person

10:25 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Interpreter sworn.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs the defendant of his/her right to an attorney.  Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  DA recites agreement, upon plea to count 1, will dismiss the domestic abuse enhancer and recommend a fine & costs and count 2 will be dismissed.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1, strikes the domestic abuse enhancer and orders count 2 be dismissed outright.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms comfirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-$100 fine plus court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court orders the cash bond be applied to the fine and costs.

Court adjourned at 10:37 a.m.
